t%20a%20company.%20He%20made%20the%20comment%20during%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DlXLBTBBil2U%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einterview%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20Stanford's%20Graduate%20School%20of%20Business%20on%20Tuesday.%20Huang's%20rationale%20is%20that%20those%20who%20report%20to%20the%20CEO%20(theoretically)%20require%20the%20least%20amount%20of%20oversight%2C%20so%20CEOs%20have%20more%20bandwidth%20than%20other%20managers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20taking%20on%20more%20direct%20reports%20could%20help%20CEOs%20level%20the%20playing%20field%2C%20too.%20According%20to%20Huang%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcommunication-business-skill-2018-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emore%20people%20a%20CEO%20directly%20communicates%20with%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20less%20likely%20an%20employee's%20stance%20at%20a%20company%20will%20be%20determined%20by%20their%20access%20to%20critical%20information.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20believe%20in%20a%20culture%2C%20in%20an%20environment%2C%20where%20the%20information%20you%20possess%20is%20the%20reason%20why%20you%20have%20power%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Huang's%20view%2C%20the%20role%20of%20the%20managers%20is%20not%20to%20broker%20power%20between%20workers%20but%20to%20collectively%20motivate%20the%20company's%20workforce.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20position%20at%20the%20company%20should%20have%20something%20to%20do%20with%20our%20ability%20to%20reason%20through%20complicated%20things%2C%20lead%20other%20people%20to%20achieve%20greatness%2C%20inspire%2C%20empower%20other%20people%2C%20support%20other%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThose%20are%20the%20reasons%20why%20the%20management%20team%20exists%2C%20in%20service%20of%20all%20the%20other%20people%20that%20work%20at%20the%20company.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnvidia-just-showed-world-ai-daddy-now-chips-revenues-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAI%20chipmaker%20has%20captured%20headlines%3C%2Fa%3E%20since%20it%20announced%20its%20blockbuster%20earnings%20for%20the%20fourth%20quarter%20of%202023%20late%20last%20month.%20And%20while%20Huang%20manages%20more%20people%20than%20other%20big-name%20CEOs%20(%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-s-team-ceo-andy-jassy-direct-reports-alexa-exec-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmazon%20CEO%20Andy%20Jassy%20has%2016%20direct%20reports%3C%2Fa%3E)%2C%20Nvidia%20has%20close%20to%2030%2C000%20employees%2C%20according%20to%20a%20company%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fimages.nvidia.com%2Faem-dam%2FSolutions%2Fdocuments%2FFY2023-NVIDIA-Corporate-Responsibility-Report-1.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%202023.%20So%2C%20Huang%20is%20only%20overseeing%20a%20small%20fraction%20of%20Nvidia's%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Huang%20might%20be%20an%20outlier%20(and%20overachiever)%20as%20a%20manager%2C%20the%20number%20of%20direct%20reports%20CEOs%20are%20taking%20on%20is%20on%20the%20rise.%20CEOs'%20direct%20reports%20doubled%20from%20five%20in%20the%20mid-1980s%20to%20close%20to%2010%20in%20the%20mid-2000s%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhbr.org%2F2012%2F04%2Fhow-many-direct-reports%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20the%20Harvard%20Business%20Review.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20a%20pretty%20optimal%20number.%20Hal%20Gregersen%2C%20formerly%20the%20executive%20director%20of%20the%20MIT%20Leadership%20Center%2C%20previously%20told%20BI%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapple-ceo-tim-cook-has-too-many-direct-reports-2015-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eideal%20number%20of%20direct%20reports%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20whether%20you're%20a%20CEO%20or%20lower-level%20manager%20%E2%80%94%20is%20between%20six%20and%20twelve.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%