0soldiers%20from%20the%20Bay%20of%20Bengal.%20With%20lightning%20speed%2C%20as%20if%20it%20were%20the%20army%20of%20Hulagu%20Khan%20that%20had%20in%20time%20immemorial%20decapitated%20thousands%20of%20heads%20in%20Punjab%20and%20lit%20a%20bonfire%20of%20the%20heads%20to%20warm%20itself%2C%20it%20reached%20Jhang.%20Here%20these%20mercenary%20soldiers%20impregnated%20the%20clouds%20which%20blocked%20the%20view%20between%20heaven%20and%20earth%2C%20between%20its%20occupants%20and%20me.%20They%20unleashed%20a%20flurry%20of%20tears%2C%20crying%20on%20behalf%20of%20the%20apsaras%20and%20houris%2C%20crying%20that%20a%20more%20beautiful%20creature%20now%20existed%20on%20earth%2C%20in%20Jhang.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Chenab%20was%20fuming%20with%20rage.%20As%20if%20intoxicated%2C%20she%20swirled%20like%20a%20bull%20in%20heat.%20She%20had%20to%20see%20for%20herself%2C%20make%20sure%20that%20the%20rumours%20were%20true.%20Daughter%20of%20the%20great%20Himalayas%2C%20the%20home%20of%20Shiva%2C%20the%20ascetic%2C%20the%20ultimate%20%3Cem%3Ejogi%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20she%20had%20been%20hearing%20stories%20through%20her%20long%20arduous%20journey%2C%20in%20search%20of%20her%20lover%2C%20whom%20she%20had%20promised%20to%20meet%20at%20the%20Sindh%20coast.%20She%20raced%20in%20the%20direction%20of%20Jhang.%20Oblivious%20to%20the%20pain%20of%20separation%20that%20her%20lover%20experienced%20in%20her%20absence%2C%20she%20headed%20off%20now%20in%20a%20different%20direction.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20310px)%2085vw%2C%20310px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F08174651%2FScreen-Shot-2024-03-08-at-5.46.21-PM.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22310%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F08174651%2FScreen-Shot-2024-03-08-at-5.46.21-PM.png%20313w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F08174651%2FScreen-Shot-2024-03-08-at-5.46.21-PM-194x300.png%20194w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-700820%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22479%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ECover%20photo%20of%20From%20Waris%20to%20Heer%3A%20A%20Novel%20of%20Punjab.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20reaching%20her%20destination%2C%20finally%20reaching%20Jhang%2C%20she%20prostrated%20outside%20its%20tall%20towers%2C%20its%20tall%20buildings%20and%20its%20tall%20mound.%20She%20pleaded%20and%20begged%20for%20just%20one%20sight%20of%20her%20Heer%2C%20for%20whom%20she%20had%20broken%20her%20journey%2C%20for%20whom%20she%20had%20delayed%20her%20union.%20Like%20an%20invading%20force%20of%20Afghans%20marching%20into%20Punjab%2C%20she%20had%20progressed%20uninterrupted%2C%20until%20she%20had%20reached%20Jhang%2C%20the%20crown%20jewel%20of%20all%20cities%2C%20glorious%20as%20Lahore%20was%20once.%20If%20only%20someone%20had%20stopped%20the%20Afghans%20the%20way%20Jhang%20halted%20her%20journey%2C%20the%20way%20Jhang%20humbled%20her.%20She%20had%20come%20not%20as%20a%20conqueror%20but%20as%20a%20beggar%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMy%20father%2C%20the%20most%20kind-hearted%20man%2C%20sire%20to%20the%20most%20beautiful%20girl%20in%20the%20world%2C%20could%20not%20ignore%20her%20wishes.%20He%20took%20Chenab%E2%80%99s%20hand%20in%20his%20own%2C%20placed%20a%20little%20flood%20water%20in%20the%20palm%20of%20his%20hand%20and%20poured%20it%20over%20my%20forehead%2C%20as%20if%20this%20was%20not%20the%20water%20of%20the%20Chenab%20but%20of%20the%20Ganga%20or%20the%20Abe%20Zamzam.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20caressed%20my%20face%20and%20ran%20her%20fingers%20through%20my%20hair.%20She%20was%20assured%20that%20the%20rumours%20were%20true.%20That%20I%20was%20indeed%20the%20most%20beautiful%20girl%20ever%20to%20be%20born%20in%20Punjab.%20For%20if%20there%20is%20a%20river%20that%20knows%20beauty%2C%20then%20it%20is%20indeed%20the%20Chenab.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20that%20fateful%20night%2C%20as%20she%20held%20my%20face%20in%20her%20hands%2C%20she%20saw%20before%20her%20eyes%20the%20unfolding%20of%20my%20complete%20life.%20She%20had%20already%20become%20a%20participant%20in%20the%20love%20story%20of%20Punjab.%20She%20changed%20her%20direction%20permanently%20that%20day%20so%20that%20she%20could%20see%20for%20herself%20this%20immortal%20love%20legend%20that%20was%20to%20unfold%20on%20her%20banks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFlowers%20bloomed%20on%20the%20land%20that%20had%20been%20blessed%20by%20the%20daughter%20of%20the%20Himalayas%20as%20she%20receded%20to%20continue%20towards%20her%20beloved.%20All%20these%20flowers%20faced%20Jhang%2C%20for%20they%20too%20wanted%20to%20see%20the%20most%20beautiful%20thing%20there%20was%20to%20see.%20These%20flowers%20did%20not%20have%20to%20wait%20for%20spring%20to%20come.%20They%20smiled%2C%20sang%20and%20danced%20in%20the%20breeze%20and%20celebrated%20%3Cem%3Ebasant%20%3C%2Fem%3Ethe%20day%20I%20stepped%20on%20the%20ground.%20The%20trees%20turned%20greener%20and%20their%20shadows%20became%20darker.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAssured%20by%20my%20laughter%2C%20the%20sun%20rose%20from%20the%20east.%20Throughout%20the%20day%2C%20it%20travelled%20through%20the%20sky%20to%20catch%20a%20glimpse%20of%20me%20from%20different%20angles.%20The%20moon%20existed%20to%20guard%20me.%20All%20night%20long%2C%20it%20kept%20the%20world%20illuminated%2C%20on%20the%20lookout%20for%20anything%20or%20anyone%20who%20could%20threaten%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20had%20spent%20many%20nights%20with%20the%20moon%20in%20its%20loneliness.%20I%20had%20lent%20it%20my%20ear%20to%20hear%20its%20tale%20of%20woe.%20Sometimes%20when%20it%20had%20cried%20to%20its%20heart%E2%80%99s%20content%2C%20it%20stared%20back%20at%20me%20with%20enquiring%20eyes%2C%20urging%20me%20to%20share%20with%20its%20lonely%20heart%20some%20stories%20of%20my%20misery.%20I%20had%20nothing%20to%20share%2C%20nothing%20to%20cry%20about.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20with%20the%20moon%2C%20I%20did%20not%20have%20the%20heart%20to%20tell%20it%20that%20I%20had%20no%20complaints%20in%20the%20house%20of%20Chuchak.%20I%20could%20never%20summon%20up%20the%20courage%20to%20tell%20it%20that%20I%20did%20not%20need%20any%20protection.%20I%20did%20not%20tell%20the%20moon%20the%20tales%20of%20my%20fierce%20character%2C%20of%20my%20bravery.%20I%20had%20waged%20wars%20and%20led%20armies%20in%20the%3Cem%3E%20qissa%3C%2Fem%3E%20penned%20by%20Damodar.%20That%20battle%20is%20not%20part%20of%20this%20qissa%20so%20I%20will%20not%20delve%20into%20it%20any%20further.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20fight%20armies%20in%20this%20qissa%20being%20penned%20by%20our%20Waris%2C%20I%20still%20retain%20my%20valour.%20I%20am%20a%20symbol%20of%20beauty%20and%20pride%2C%20but%20don%E2%80%99t%20forget%20that%20I%20am%20also%20a%20metaphor%20for%20rebellion%2C%20for%20action%20and%20agency.%20Our%20Ranjha%20might%20be%20the%20symbol%20of%20the%20divine%2C%20but%20what%20will%20happen%20to%20the%20divine%20if%20there%20is%20no%20devotee%3F%20Would%20the%20divine%20be%20able%20to%20retain%20its%20divinity%2C%20if%20that%20divinity%20is%20not%20recognised%2C%20not%20worshipped%3F%20The%20divine%20is%20an%20object%20of%20worship%20and%20without%20being%20worshipped%2C%20it%20is%20nothing%20but%20an%20object.%20It%20is%20through%20the%20finite%20nature%20of%20the%20devotee%20that%20the%20infinity%20of%20the%20divine%20is%20recognised.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20devotee%20is%20not%20a%20helpless%2C%20passive%20partner%20in%20this%20relationship%2C%20but%20rather%20the%20agent%2C%20the%20shaper%20of%20events%2C%20who%20makes%20this%20relationship%20progress.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDon%E2%80%99t%20be%20mistaken.%20This%20is%20not%20the%20story%20of%20Heer%E2%80%93Ranjha%20but%20rather%20the%20story%20of%20Heer%20%E2%80%94%20Waris%E2%80%99s%20Heer%2C%20from%20Waris%20to%20Heer.%20You%20might%20be%20tempted%20to%20see%20the%20parallels%20between%20Ranjha%20and%20our%20poet%2C%20our%20creator%2C%20our%20Waris%2C%20but%20it%20is%20really%20I%20who%20truly%20represent%20him.%20It%20is%20in%20my%20voice%20that%20the%20devotees%20speak%20%E2%80%94%20from%20Shah%20Hussain%20to%20Bulleh%20Shah%2C%20and%20now%20Waris.%20Sometimes%20I%20take%20the%20form%20of%20Radha%2C%20sometimes%20that%20of%20a%20nameless%20housewife%2C%20but%20it%20is%20always%20I%2C%20at%20the%20centre%20of%20it%20all%2C%20who%20become%20the%20symbol%20of%20a%20Sufi%2C%20a%20devotee%2C%20while%20Ranjha%20becomes%20the%20symbol%20of%20the%20divine.%20I%20make%20possible%20the%20union%20between%20the%20devotee%20and%20the%20divine%2C%20the%20disintegration%20of%20the%20male%20in%20my%20female%20body.%20For%20neither%20is%20there%20a%20distinction%20between%20a%20devotee%20and%20the%20divine%2C%20nor%20is%20there%20any%20distinction%20between%20the%20male%20and%20the%20female.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20am%20Waris%20and%20Waris%20is%20Heer.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709987386000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F08180545%2FScreen-Shot-2024-03-08-at-6.04.56-PM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fbook-excerpt-the-immortal-legend-of-wariss-heer%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22I%20had%20spent%20many%20nights%20with%20the%20moon%20in%20its%20loneliness.%20I%20had%20lent%20it%20my%20ear%20to%20hear%20its%20tale%20of%20woe.%20Sometimes%20when%20it%20had%20cried%20to%20its%20heart%E2%80%99s%20content%2C%20it%20stared%20back%20at%20me%20with%20enquiring%20eyes%2C%20urging%20me%20to%20share%20with%20its%20lonely%20heart%20some%20stories%20of%20my%20misery.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fbook-excerpt-the-immortal-legend-of-wariss-heer%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22PM%20Modi%20unveils%20infra%20projects%20worth%20Rs%204%2C500%20cr%20in%20northern%20West%20Bengal%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22pu