%20Delhi%E2%80%99s%20clampdown.%20Waheed-ur-Rehman%20Para%2C%20a%2034-year-old%20leader%20from%20the%20People%E2%80%99s%20Democratic%20Party%20(PDP)%2C%20one%20of%20the%20region%E2%80%99s%20two%20major%20political%20formations%2C%20was%20once%20considered%20a%20potential%20chief%20minister%20thanks%20to%20the%20backing%20he%20enjoyed%20in%20New%20Delhi.%20In%202020%2C%20however%2C%20he%20was%20arrested%20under%20anti-terror%20laws%20and%2C%20according%20to%20a%20team%20of%20UN%20experts%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aljazeera.com%2Fnews%2F2021%2F6%2F3%2Fpro-india-kashmiri-politician-tortured-in-custody-say-un-experts%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etortured%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20before%20being%20released%20on%20bail%20after%20seventeen%20months%20in%20jail.%20He%20continues%20to%20fight%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.telegraphindia.com%2Findia%2Fnia-court-denies-peoples-democratic-party-leader-waheed-ur-rehman-para-permission-to-travel-outside-jammu-and-kashmir-for-fathers-treatment%2Fcid%2F1970191%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eterror%20charges%20in%20court%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0and%20is%20not%20allowed%20to%20travel%20outside%20the%20region.%20His%20perceptions%20of%20the%20Indian%20state%20have%20undergone%20a%20corresponding%20sea%20change.%20%E2%80%9CI%20used%20to%20believe%20that%20the%20sky%20was%20the%20limit%20for%20a%20Kashmiri%20Muslim%20in%20India%E2%80%9D%2C%20he%20says.%20%E2%80%9CNow%20I%20have%20lost%20all%20hope%E2%80%9D.%20Seeing%20Kashmiris%20of%20all%20political%20and%20ideological%20hues%20%E2%80%93%20from%20those%20who%20worked%20for%20the%20Indian%20state%20to%20those%20who%20fought%20it%20%E2%80%93%20living%20together%20in%20the%20same%20jail%20convinced%20him%20that%2C%20in%20the%20end%2C%20the%20Indian%20state%20treats%20all%20Kashmiris%20the%20same%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F09%2F30153604%2FScreen-Shot-2019-09-30-at-3.35.42-PM.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F09%2F30153604%2FScreen-Shot-2019-09-30-at-3.35.42-PM.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F09%2F30153604%2FScreen-Shot-2019-09-30-at-3.35.42-PM-300x113.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F09%2F30153604%2FScreen-Shot-2019-09-30-at-3.35.42-PM-1024x387.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-401251%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22453%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EFile%20images%20of%20J%26amp%3BK%20mainstream%20politicians%2C%20Farooq%20Abdullah%2C%20Sajad%20Lone%2C%20Mehbooba%20Mufti%20and%20Omar%20Abdullah.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPro-India%20politicians%20in%20the%20region%20often%20characterised%20their%20role%20as%20intermediaries%20between%20New%20Delhi%20and%20Kashmiri%20civil%20society.%20Para%20himself%20used%20to%20be%20a%20flagbearer%20of%20Indian%20democracy%20among%20young%20people%20in%20the%20region.%20He%20was%20credited%20with%20persuading%20many%20of%20them%20to%20take%20part%20in%20elections.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20wanted%20to%20marginalise%20militancy%20as%20an%20ideology%20by%20bringing%20dignity%20to%20democracy%E2%80%9D%2C%20he%20recalls.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20used%20to%20look%20at%20elections%20as%20a%20process%20of%20countering%20violence%E2%80%9D.%20But%20the%20absence%20of%20an%20elected%20regional%20government%20has%20left%20Kashmiris%20with%20nowhere%20to%20turn%20to%20address%20their%20grievances%20and%20stoked%20resentment%20of%20the%20federal%20government.%20Kashmiris%E2%80%99%20desperation%20is%20visible%20at%20political%20party%20offices%20in%20Srinagar%2C%20where%20people%20queue%20to%20seek%20help%20with%20their%20day-to-day%20problems%20even%20though%20the%20politicians%20there%20have%20virtually%20no%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMounting%20pressure%20for%20elections%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EAgainst%20this%20backdrop%2C%20and%20for%20the%20first%20time%20ever%2C%20Kashmir%E2%80%99s%20two%20political%20lineages%20%E2%80%93%20pro-India%20and%20separatist%20%E2%80%93%20are%20both%20demanding%20elections%20for%20the%20promised%20regional%20assembly.%20Their%20alignment%20on%20the%20issue%20of%20polls%20is%20nothing%20less%20than%20historic%2C%20even%20if%20some%20of%20the%20most%20hardline%20separatists%20remain%20outside%20the%20emerging%20consensus.%20The%20call%20for%20elections%20is%20a%20position%20that%20enjoys%20support%20from%20outside%20the%20regional%20political%20establishment%20as%20well%3B%20the%20Kashmiris%20Crisis%20Group%20spoke%20to%20were%20united%20in%20calling%20for%20elections%20at%20the%20earliest%20possible%20moment.%20This%20plea%20is%20all%20the%20more%20extraordinary%20given%20the%20mistrust%20of%20polls%20in%20the%20past%2C%20with%20central%20government%20interference%20and%20manipulation%20in%20elections%20a%20constant%20since%20independence%20in%201947.%20It%20was%20precisely%20such%20manipulation%20of%20the%201987%20regional%20elections%20that%20led%20to%20the%20birth%20of%20a%20separatist%20insurgency%2C%20and%20since%20then%2C%20militants%20and%20separatist%20politicians%20have%20systematically%20exerted%20their%20clout%20to%20ensure%20that%20participation%20rates%20remained%20abysmal%20%E2%80%93%20at%20times%20as%20low%20as%206%20per%20cent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EPoliticians%20who%20have%20always%20boycotted%20elections%2C%20and%20called%20upon%20all%20Kashmiris%20to%20follow%20suit%2C%20are%20now%20demanding%20that%20polls%20be%20held%20as%20a%20way%20to%20protest%20what%20they%20consider%20to%20be%20Indian%20occupation.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20had%20our%20differences%20with%20%5Bthe%20mainstream%20parties%5D%E2%80%9D%2C%20notes%20Mirwaiz%20Umar%20Farooq%2C%20Kashmir%E2%80%99s%20chief%20cleric%20and%20chairman%20of%20the%20Hurriyat%20Conference%2C%20a%20coalition%20of%20moderate%20separatist%20social%20and%20political%20outfits.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20looked%20at%20them%20as%20those%20who%20could%20administer%20and%20govern%20day-to-day%20issues%2C%20but%20they%20never%20represented%20the%20sentiments%20of%20the%20people.%20Farooq%2C%20who%20has%20spent%20much%20of%20the%20last%20five%20years%20under%20house%20arrest%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fmirwaiz-delivers-friday-sermon-after-4-years-calls-for-dialogue-reconciliation%2Farticle67334575.ece%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eadds%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20%E2%80%9CIn%20hindsight%2C%20I%20believe%20it%20was%20wrong%20on%20our%20part%20to%20call%20for%20boycotts%20of%20past%20elections%E2%80%9D.%20Now%2C%20he%20is%20%E2%80%9Cencouraging%20people%20to%20fight%20politically%20and%20peacefully%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20central%20BJP%20government%20has%20taken%20steps%20to%20prepare%20for%20regional%20elections%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%2C%20although%20not%20all%20of%20them%20are%20welcome.%20In%20particular%2C%20residents%20worry%20that%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fforeignpolicy.com%2F2021%2F08%2F11%2Fmodi-is-trying-to-engineer-a-hindu-majority-in-kashmir%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBJP%20is%20skewing%20the%20system%20to%20its%20political%20advantage%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20March%202020%2C%20New%20Delhi%20initiated%20a%20process%20to%20demarcate%20new%20constituencies%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir.%20In%20the%20end%2C%20six%20new%20constituencies%20were%20added%20to%20the%20Jammu%20division%2C%20with%20a%20population%20of%205.3%20million%2C%20while%20only%20one%20was%20added%20to%20the%20Kashmir%20division%2C%20which%20has%206.8%20million%20people.%20For%20most%20Kashmiri%20political%20parties%20and%20much%20of%20the%20public%2C%20this%20measure%20confirmed%20the%20suspicion%20that%20the%20central%20government%E2%80%99s%20objective%20is%20to%20boost%20the%20number%20of%20seats%20in%20non-Muslim%20majority%20areas%20of%20the%20state%2C%20since%20Jammu%20has%20a%20majority-Hindu%20population%2C%20while%20the%20Kashmir%20valley%20is%2097%20per%20cent%20Muslim.%20The%20BJP%20hopes%20that%20the%20numerical%20heft%20given%20to%20the%20Jammu%20region%20will%20help%20it%20achieve%20a%20majority%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%2C%20allowing%20it%20to%20form%20a%20regional%20government%20with%20its%20own%20chief%20minister%20at%20the%20helm%2C%20without%20depending%20on%20a%20coalition%20that%20would%20need%20to%20include%20Kashmiri%20regional%20parties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKashmir%E2%80%99s%20political%20leaders%20have%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farticle-14.com%2Fpost%2Fkashmir-s-new-electoral-map-boosts-hindu-electoral-influence-reduces-muslim-representation-625c729a74c8b%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edenounced%20the%20move%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0as%20a%20deliberate%20attempt%20to%20engineer%20a%20victory%20for%20the%20BJP%2C%20with%20the%20objective%20of%20achieving%20the%20election%20of%20a%20Hindu%20chief%20minister%20in%20the%20region%20for%20the%20first%20time.%20%E2%80%9CThey%20have%20already%20rigged%20the%20elections%20even%20before%20they%20are%20held%20%E2%80%A6%20to%20further%20disempower%20Kashmiris%E2%80%9D%2C%20declared%20former%20chief%20minister%20and%20PDP%20president%20Mehbooba%20Mufti.%20In%20an%20apparent%20bid%20to%20weaken%20existing%20regional%20parties%2C%20New%20Delhi%20has%20also%20propped%20up%20newer%20pro-India%20formations.%20But%20while%20these%20new%20parties%20have%20been%20somewhat%20successful%20in%20poaching%20from%20the%20ranks%20of%20traditional%20parties%20%E2%80%93%20the%20PDP%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20has%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Fpolitics-and-nation%2Fafter-exodus-of-top-leaders-pdp-launches-online-campaign-to-strengthen-presence-in-j-k-politics%2Farticleshow%2F102112988.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elost%20over%2040%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0senior%20members%20since%202020%20%E2%80%93%20they%20are%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscroll.in%2Farticle%2F1032825%2Fwhy-ghulam-nabi-azads-new-party-has-been-met-with-scepticism-in-kashmir%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estruggling%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0to%20generate%20popular%20support%2C%20as%20many%20Kashmiris%20consider%20them%20to%20be%20BJP%20proxies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EMany%20Kashmiri%20leaders%20and%20analysts%20assert%20that%20the%20main%20reason%20New%20Delhi%20has%20not%20yet%20announced%20a%20date%20for%20the%20long-awaited%20regional%20elections%20is%20that%20it%20cannot%20yet%20be%20sure%20that%20the%20BJP%20or%20its%20proxies%20will%20do%20sufficiently%20well.%20%E2%80%9C%5BElections%5D%20is%20one%20place%20where%20people%20can%20give%20vent%20to%20the%20feelings%E2%80%9D%2C%20said%20former%20chief%20minister%20Abdullah.%20%E2%80%9CBy%20voting%20against%20the%20BJP%20or%20parties%20perceived%20close%20to%20it%2C%20they%20can%20make%20known%20their%20unhappiness%20about%20the%20state%20of%20affairs%20post-August%202019%E2%80%9D.%20It%20is%20also%20likely%20that%20the%20BJP%20does%20not%20want%20to%20risk%20losing%20regional%20elections%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20ahead%20of%20national%20elections%20beginning%20in%20April%2C%20when%20Prime%20Minister%20Modi%20will%20be%20seeking%20a%20third%20term.%20(National%20elections%20will%20be%20contested%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20as%20elsewhere%20in%20the%20country.)%20The%20central%20government%E2%80%99s%20reluctance%20to%20test%20the%20regional%20electorate%20has%20even%20extended%20to%20elections%20for%20municipal%20bodies%20and%20village%20tracts%2C%20which%20are%20also%20overdue.%20India%E2%80%99s%20chief%20election%20commissioner%20has%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnbctv18.com%2Fpolitics%2Felection-jammu-kashmir-right-time-keeping-security-situation-commission-17993511.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edefended%20the%20delay%3C%2Fa%3Es%C2%A0on%20the%20basis%20of%20security%20conditions%20in%20the%20region%2C%20but%20a%20senior%20police%20officer%20says%20the%20real%20reasons%20are%20political.%20%E2%80%9CIf%20the%20central%20government%20could%20hold%20elections%20in%201996%20and%201998%2C%20when%20militancy%20was%20at%20its%20peak%2C%20it%20should%20not%20be%20difficult%20to%20do%20so%20now%E2%80%9D%2C%20he%20observed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThere%20is%2C%20however%2C%20pressure%20on%20the%20government%20to%20bring%20the%20delays%20to%20an%20end.%20On%20December%2011%2C%202023%2C%20while%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fopinion%2Feditorial%2Fominously-anti-federal-on-the-supreme-courts-judgement-on-article-370-and-jks-special-status%2Farticle67628150.ece%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eupholding%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%202019%20decision%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20restructure%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20directed%20the%20election%20commission%20to%20conduct%20regional%20polls%20before%20September%2030%2C%202024.%20But%20notwithstanding%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20decision%2C%20the%20choice%20of%20election%20day%20will%20hinge%20on%20a%20risk%20assessment%20by%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20national%20security%20agencies%2C%20which%20could%20become%20a%20pretext%20for%20continuing%20delay.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EOn%20March%207%2C%20Prime%20Minister%20Modi%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fpm-modi-in-srinagar-says-jk-touching-new-heights-of-development-after-article-370-abrogation%2Farticle67924063.ece%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evisited%20Kashmir%20for%20the%20first%20time%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0since%20the%20momentous%20changes%20of%20August%202019%20to%20address%20a%20public%20meeting%20in%20Srinagar%2C%20with%20an%20eye%20to%20the%20forthcoming%20national%20elections.%20The%20BJP%20is%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscroll.in%2Farticle%2F1064793%2Fa-message-for-mainland-in-kashmir-few-expectations-ahead-of-modis-first-visit-after-august-2019%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehoping%20to%20register%20a%20win%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0for%20the%20first%20time%20ever%20in%20Kashmir.%20Modi%20announced%20a%20few%20development%20projects%20and%20asserted%20that%20Kashmir%E2%80%99s%20prosperity%20is%20peaking%20after%20the%20abrogation%20of%20Article%20370.%20He%20said%20nothing%20of%20his%20promises%20regarding%20statehood%20or%20regional%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESeizing%20the%20opportunity%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EIt%20would%20be%20in%20New%20Delhi%E2%80%99s%20interest%20to%20proceed%20with%20the%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20regional%20polls%20at%20the%20earliest%20opportunity.%20Ideally%2C%20they%20would%20be%20held%20well%20before%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20September%20deadline%2C%20and%20regardless%20of%20whether%20there%20are%20national%20polls%20in%20the%20spring%2C%20which%20will%20likely%20do%20little%20more%20than%20ensconce%20the%20BJP%20more%20deeply%20in%20power.%20By%20allowing%20Kashmiris%20to%20choose%20electoral%20representatives%20who%20can%20speak%20on%20their%20behalf%2C%20both%20for%20a%20regional%20assembly%20and%20for%20municipalities%20and%C2%A0%3Cem%3Epanchayats%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0(the%20lowest%20rung%20of%20the%20Indian%20administrative%20system)%2C%20regional%20and%20local%20polls%20would%20help%20counter%20the%20growing%20perception%20among%20locals%20that%20they%20are%20being%20singled%20out%20for%20a%20kind%20of%20%E2%80%9Ccollective%20punishment%E2%80%9D%20and%20have%20no%20political%20capacity%20to%20improve%20their%20lot%3B%20this%20sentiment%20can%20only%20stoke%20the%20frustrations%20of%20Kashmiri%20youth%2C%20potentially%20multiplying%20militant%20ranks%20%E2%80%93%20which%20Indian%20officials%20concede.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20in%20the%20fourth%20decade%20of%20militancy%20and%20have%20brought%20it%20under%20control%20to%20a%20large%20extent%E2%80%9D%2C%20a%20senior%20counter-insurgency%20official%20confided.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20time%20for%20punitive%20action%20is%20over%2C%20now%20is%20the%20time%20for%20a%20policy%20to%20offer%20carrots.%20Punitive%20action%20alone%20can%E2%80%99t%20bring%20peace%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fread-the-caravans-article-on-army-torture-the-union-government-wants-taken-down%5C%22%3EThe%20Caravan%E2%80%99s%20Article%20on%20Army%20Torture%20the%20Union%20Government%20Wants%20Taken%20Down%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EUnprecedented%20tacit%20support%20from%20some%20separatist%20parties%20for%20elections%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20presents%20an%20important%20opportunity%20that%20the%20Indian%20government%20should%20grasp.%20After%20decades%20of%20electoral%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fjammu-and-kashmir-local-body-polls%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eboycotts%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0of%20the%20vote%2C%20New%20Delhi%20should%20capitalise%20on%20the%20endorsement%20that%20both%20mainstream%20and%20separatist%20forces%20have%20made%20of%20the%20electoral%20process%2C%20which%20could%20promote%20higher%20turnout%20%E2%80%93%20even%20if%20separatist%20candidates%20do%20not%20themselves%20stand%20for%20election.%20%E2%80%9CI%20have%20been%20trying%20to%20convey%20to%20the%20government%20of%20India%20that%20the%20story%20coming%20out%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20should%20not%20be%20about%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20victory%2C%20but%20about%20high%20participation%20in%20elections.%20Why%20%5Bis%20the%20government%5D%20focused%20on%20selling%20the%20success%20of%20a%20party%20to%20the%20world%3F%20Sell%20the%20fact%20that%20for%20the%20first%20time%20after%201990%2C%20you%20had%20an%20election%20where%2040-60%20percent%20of%20the%20population%20turned%20out%20to%20vote%E2%80%9D%2C%20Abdullah%20said.%20There%20is%20some%20risk%20of%20violence%20against%20candidates%2C%20but%20the%20burden%20should%20be%20on%20the%20national%20government%20to%20prove%20that%20it%20is%20sufficient%20to%20postpone%20polls.%20Thus%20far%2C%20the%20evidence%20is%20not%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EAs%20a%20confidence-building%20gesture%20before%20any%20campaign%20begins%2C%20New%20Delhi%20should%20at%20least%20provide%20Kashmir%E2%80%99s%20pro-India%20politicians%20with%20the%20space%20to%20carry%20out%20normal%20political%20activity%2C%20including%20the%20right%20to%20free%20speech%20and%20assembly.%20Local%20political%20leaders%20should%20be%20allowed%20to%20travel%20and%20attend%20public%20meetings%20without%20restrictions%2C%20and%20arbitrary%20detentions%20of%20politicians%20in%20their%20own%20homes%20should%20cease%20immediately.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EElections%20on%20their%20own%2C%20however%2C%20will%20not%20be%20enough%20to%20calm%20the%20tensions%20in%20Kashmir.%20New%20Delhi%20needs%20to%20engage%20in%20a%20sustained%2C%20meaningful%20political%20process%20to%20address%20rising%20alienation.%20Such%20a%20process%20can%20only%20start%20with%20a%20dialogue%20with%20the%20Kashmiri%20political%20class%20%E2%80%93%20including%20separatists%20%E2%80%93%20and%20civil%20society%20at%20large%2C%20including%20religious%20leaders%20and%20other%20influential%20public%20representatives.%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Findia%2Fno-talks-with-hurriyat-jamiat-pakistan-home-minister-amit-shah-2641588%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEngaging%20separatists%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0will%20be%20challenging%2C%20particularly%20given%20the%20ruling%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20hawkish%20political%20outlook%20on%20these%20issues%2C%20but%20back-channel%20diplomacy%20with%20Pakistan%20offers%20a%20way%20forward%20for%20discreet%20engagement%2C%20given%20Islamabad%E2%80%99s%20influence%20over%20many%20of%20them.%20In%202019-2020%2C%20such%20back%20channels%2C%20mediated%20by%20the%20United%20Arab%20Emirates%2C%20saw%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Fchina%2Fexclusive-indian-pakistan-held-secret-talks-try-break-kashmir-impasse-2021-04-14%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIndia%20and%20Pakistan%20recommit%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0to%20a%20floundering%20ceasefire%20despite%20severe%20bilateral%20tensions%20at%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3ETo%20make%20the%20most%20of%20the%20political%20moment%2C%20the%20Modi%20government%20would%20ideally%20also%20restore%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%E2%80%99s%20statehood%20before%20holding%20regional%20elections.%20Under%20the%20Indian%20constitution%2C%20statehood%20grants%20a%20degree%20of%20federal%20autonomy%20that%20empowers%20regional%20governments%2C%20allowing%20them%20to%20address%20public%20demands%20more%20effectively.%20The%202019%20decision%20to%20downgrade%20the%20state%20to%20a%20union%20territory%2C%20which%20is%20extremely%20rare%20in%20Indian%20history%2C%20hurt%20both%20local%20governance%20and%20Kashmiris%E2%80%99%20pride.%20Since%20then%2C%20the%20Indian%20government%20%E2%80%93%20led%20by%20Modi%20himself%20%E2%80%93%20has%20promised%20to%20restore%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%E2%80%99s%20statehood%20several%20times%2C%20albeit%20with%20redefined%20borders%20since%20Ladakh%20has%20been%20carved%20out%20as%20a%20separate%20union%20territory.%20But%20it%20has%20yet%20to%20announce%20any%20concrete%20steps.%20Upon%20receiving%20a%20Supreme%20Court%20ruling%20in%20December%20that%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Fpolitics-and-nation%2Fconduct-elections-of-jk-assembly-by-september-30-2024-sc-directs-election-commission%2Farticleshow%2F105894031.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edirected%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0it%20to%20move%20ahead%20with%20restoring%20regional%20statehood%2C%20the%20government%20said%20it%20would%20do%20so%20at%20an%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Findia%2Frestoration-of-statehood-of-jk-at-appropriate-time-amit-shah-in-rs-2806509%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eappropriate%20time%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20lack%20of%20urgency%20is%20unfortunate.%20Veterans%20of%20Kashmir%E2%80%99s%20troubled%20history%20warn%20that%20unless%20the%20basics%20of%20political%20participation%20and%20civic%20freedoms%20are%20in%20place%2C%20New%20Delhi%E2%80%99s%20narrative%20of%20peace%20and%20security%20will%20be%20increasingly%20challenged%20by%20regional%20unrest.%20The%20warning%20signs%20are%20now%20evident.%20In%20the%20words%20of%20chief%20cleric%20Farooq%2C%20%E2%80%9CThey%20are%20pushing%20the%20next%20generation%20of%20Kashmiris%20to%20the%20wall%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709976599000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F10152019%2F27423964742_c550b3b390_k.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fmodi-govt-must-engage-with-kashmir-as-elections-alone-wont-address-brewing-discontent%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20the%20eyes%20of%20many%20Kashmiris%2C%20the%20Modi%20government%20has%20turned%20Kashmir%20into%20a%20'police%20state'%20where%20arbitrary%20detentions%2C%20high%20levels%20of%20incarceration%20and%20constant%20surveillance%20have%20generated%20a%20climate%20of%20pervasive%20fear.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A12%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fmodi-govt-must-engage-with-kashmir-as-elections-alone-wont-address-brewing-discontent%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Bihar%3A%20Why%20Upcoming%20Lok%20Sabha%20Polls%20Could%20Spell%20Doom%20for%20Nitish%20Kumar%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F28163221%2F400924413_926965212122173_7713585483950685171_n.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EElection%20strategist%20turned%20activist%20Prashant%20Kishor%20predicts%20a%20%E2%80%98doom%E2%80%99%20for%20Nitish%20Kumar%20and%20the%20%E2%80%98rise%E2%80%99%20of%20Narendra%20Modi%20in%20the%202024%20Lok%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%2047%20year-%20old%20with%20a%20unique%20distinction%20to%20strategise%20the%20elections%20of%20both%20Nitish%20and%20Modi%20apart%20from%20several%20other%20top%20leaders%20from%20their%20war-rooms%2C%20has%20morphed%20him%20into%20a%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3Epadyatri%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E(footslogger)%E2%80%99%2C%20carrying%20out%20his%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3EJan%20Suraj%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0%3Cem%3EAbhiyan%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0(good%20governance%20campaign)%E2%80%99%20at%20the%20grassroots%20level%20in%20Bihar%20for%20the%20last%2017%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOf%20late%2C%20he%20has%20become%20a%20toast%20of%20varied%20news%20outlets%20giving%20interviews%20and%20assessing%20and%20predicting%20the%20prospects%20of%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20%3Cem%3Evis-a-vis%3C%2Fem%3E%20others%20in%20the%20coming%20general%20elections.%20In%20his%20assessment%20of%20Bihar%E2%80%99s%20context%2C%20the%20chief%20minister%20and%20his%20Janata%20Dal%20(United)%20will%20be%20doomed%20beyond%20redemption%20and%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20will%20hold%20his%20forte%20after%20the%20polls.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CNitish%20and%20his%20party%20have%20no%20future%20beyond%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20polls.%20The%20BJP%20swallowed%20him%20by%20hugging%20him%20back%20in%202017.%20Now%2C%20he%20is%20left%20only%20with%20his%20skeleton.%20The%20BJP%20will%20carry%20his%20skeleton%20for%20whatever%20use%20it%20has%20till%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections.%20After%20that%2C%20he%20(Nitish)%20will%20be%20done%20and%20dusted.%20They%20(BJP)%20are%20smart%20enough%20to%20deal%20with%20such%20type%20of%20leaders%2C%E2%80%9D%20Kishore%20said%20in%20a%20question-answer%20session%20at%20the%20event%20of%20a%20national%20daily%20of%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20logic%20behind%20Kishore%E2%80%99s%20claim%20is%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20larger-than-life%20persona%2C%20of%20which%20%E2%80%9CRam%2C%20Hindutva%2C%20nationalism%20and%20welfare-ism%20are%20subservient%20to%E2%80%9D%2C%20will%20drive%20the%20voters%20to%20vote%20for%20the%20BJP%2C%20propelling%20its%20prospects%20in%20the%20polls%20and%20Nitish%E2%80%99s%20party%20could%20benefit%20out%20of%20it%20in%20terms%20of%20a%20few%20seats.%20%E2%80%9CBut%20the%20BJP%20will%20have%20to%20pay%20a%20heavy%20price%20for%20carrying%20him%20along%20in%20the%202025%20assembly%20elections%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20the%20question%20is%3A%20Is%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20personality%20so%20attractive%20and%20Nitish%E2%80%99s%20so%20repulsive%3F%20Will%20the%20voters%20vote%20for%20Modi%2C%20carrying%20extreme%20detest%20for%20Nitish%20in%20their%20minds%20and%20hearts%3F%20Is%20Modi%20so%20lovable%20and%20Nitish%20so%20detestable%3F%20Will%20the%20amorphous%20voters%20be%20so%20precise%20and%20accurate%20in%20preferring%20Modi%20and%20overlooking%20Nitish%3F%20The%20JDU%20and%20the%20BJP%20had%20shared%2017%20seats%20each%20in%202019.%20By%20all%20accounts%2C%20the%20JDU%20will%20get%20the%20lion%E2%80%99s%20share%20among%20other%20National%20Democratic%20Alliance%20(NDA)%20partners%20in%20Bihar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%E2%80%99s%20a%20fact%20that%20Prashant%20Kishor%20has%20plausible%20experience%20of%20working%20at%20the%20war-rooms%20of%20the%20%E2%80%9Cwho%E2%80%99s%20who%E2%80%9D%20of%20Indian%20political%20panorama%20and%20as%20well%20as%20interacting%20with%20the%20cross-sections%20of%20the%20people%20at%20the%20grassroots%20level.%20He%20is%20supposed%20to%20have%20reasonable%20acumen%20to%20assess%20and%20predict%20the%20polls.%20What%20might%20be%20adding%20to%20the%20credence%20of%20his%20assessment%20and%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20claim%20of%20taking%20his%20alliance%E2%80%99s%20tally%20to%20%E2%80%9C400-%3Cem%3Epaar%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0(beyond%20400)%E2%80%9D%20%C2%A0is%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20stupendous%20performance%20in%20the%202019%20Lok%20Sabha%20in%20which%20it%20improved%20from%20283%20in%202014%20to%20303.%3Cstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPost-2019%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20claim%20and%20Kishor%E2%80%99s%20observations%20don%E2%80%99t%20appear%20to%20factor%20in%20the%20developments%20that%20have%20taken%20place%20after%202019.%20The%20first%20and%20foremost%20development%20in%20Bihar%E2%80%99s%20context%20is%20the%20emergence%20of%20Tejashwi%20Yadav%2C%20making%20employment%2C%20on%20which%20Modi%20has%20decidedly%20failed%2C%20the%20central%20weapon%20against%20the%20Hindutva%20party.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20it%20proved%20to%20be%20a%20potent%20weapon%20became%20evident%20when%20he%20led%20his%20Rashtriya%20Janata%20Dal%E2%80%99s%20emergence%20as%20the%20single%20largest%20party%20with%2079%20MLAs%20in%20the%20face%20of%20the%20combined%20might%20of%20the%20BJP%20and%20the%20JDU%20in%20the%202020%20assembly%20polls.%20Of%20course%2C%20the%20biggest%20casualty%20of%20Tejashwi%E2%80%99s%20rise%20was%20Nitish%E2%80%99s%20party%20which%20was%20reduced%20to%2042%20MLAs.%20But%20the%20BJP%20was%20not%20unscathed%20as%20it%20with%20its%2075%20MLAs%20got%20barely%20eight%20seats%20more%20than%20%3Cem%3EMahagathbandhan%E2%80%99s%3C%2Fem%3E%20114%20to%20form%20the%20government%20with%20Tejashwi%20missing%20the%20chance%20by%20a%20whisker.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%2C%20it%20is%20unwise%20to%20say%20that%20Tejaswhi%20succeeded%20simply%20because%20it%20was%20a%20state%20election.%20The%20PM%20had%20addressed%2032%20meetings%2C%20attacking%20Tejaswhi%20and%20ridiculing%20his%20father%20Lalu%20Prasad%20Yadav%20%E2%80%93%20in%20jail%20at%20that%20time%20%E2%80%93%20for%20promoting%20his%20progeny%20in%20politics.%20But%20the%20voters%2C%20evidently%2C%20believed%20Tejashwi%20more%20than%20Modi%20and%20Nitish%20and%20voted%20for%20the%20Tejashwi-led%20alliance.%20The%20NDA%20had%20got%20only%201%2C2000%20votes%20more%20than%20that%20of%20the%20%3Cem%3EMahagathbandhan%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0in%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F01171947%2FTejashwi-Yadav-II.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F01171947%2FTejashwi-Yadav-II.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F01171947%2FTejashwi-Yadav-II-300x200.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F01171947%2FTejashwi-Yadav-II-1024x683.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-699668%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EPhoto%3A%20X%2F%40yadavtejashwi.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETejaswhi%20had%20announced%20that%20he%20would%20give%2010%20lakh%20jobs%20if%20he%20was%20voted%20to%20power%20in%202020.%20He%20added%20credence%20to%20his%20claim%20after%20Nitish%20joined%20the%C2%A0%3Cem%3EMahagathbandhan%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%20August%202022%20and%20Tejaswhi%20became%20his%20deputy%20by%20making%20the%20CM%20hand%20about%204.50%20lakh%20jobs%20during%20the%20seventeen%20months%20of%20their%20tenure%20together%20in%20office.%20The%20mammoth%20crowd%20of%20the%20youths%20at%20his%20recently%20concluded%20Jan%20Vishwash%20Yatra%20that%20culminated%20at%20the%20Indian%20National%20Developmental%20Inclusive%20Alliance%20(INDIA)%20rally%20at%20Patna%E2%80%99s%20Gandhi%20Maidan%20on%20March%203%20amply%20reflected%20the%20hope%20and%20excitement%20of%20the%20youths.%20It%20might%20not%20be%20easy%20for%20Modi%20who%20had%20specifically%20claimed%20to%20give%20two%20crore%20jobs%20annually%20at%20his%20several%20meetings%20in%20the%20previous%20elections%20to%20outclass%20Tejaswhi%20among%20the%20unemployed%20youths.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMoreover%2C%20the%20opposition%20might%20not%20be%20as%20strong%20in%20terms%20of%20the%20control%20over%20the%20resources%2C%20institutions%20and%20media%20narrative%20as%20the%20BJP%20is.%20But%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20as%20disarrayed%20as%20it%20was%20in%202019%20either%20in%20Bihar%20or%20in%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20country.%20While%20the%20RJD-Congress-Left%20has%20a%20well-knit%20alliance%20in%20the%20state%2C%20the%20INDIA%20bloc%20has%20beefed%20up%20its%20strength%20by%20striking%20alliances%20in%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20Delhi%2C%20Gujarat%20and%20Maharashtra.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EKishor%20%3Cem%3Eversus%3C%2Fem%3E%20Tejashwi%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBe%20it%20because%20of%20%E2%80%98strategic%20reasons%E2%80%99%20or%20his%20genuine%20feelings%2C%20Prashant