Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fjustice-abhijit-gangopadhyay-politics-resignation-tmc%5C%22%3Eannounced%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20he%20will%20be%20resigning%20from%20his%20post%20to%20join%20active%20politics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGangopadhyay%2C%20who%20was%20due%20to%20retire%20in%20August%202024%2C%20is%20not%20the%20first%20judge%20in%20India%20to%20take%20early%20retirement%20to%20take%20the%20political%20plunge.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20it%20is%20this%20statement%2C%20in%20which%20Gangopadhyay%20says%20that%20he%20was%20in%20touch%20with%20the%20BJP%20and%20the%20BJP%20was%20in%20touch%20with%20him%2C%20implying%20that%20as%20a%20sitting%20judge%20he%20was%20in%20touch%20with%20a%20political%20party%2C%20that%20has%20once%20again%20raised%20questions%20of%20judicial%20propriety%2C%20independence%2C%20and%20whether%20there%20should%20be%20a%20cooling%20off%20period%20for%20judges%20before%20they%20enter%20electoral%20politics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGangopadhyay%20had%20presided%20over%20key%20judgments%20that%20criticised%20the%20Trinamool%20Congress%20(TMC)%20government%20in%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%202022%2C%20he%20was%20being%20called%20as%20the%20%E2%80%9Cpeople%E2%80%99s%20judge%E2%80%9D%20having%20posited%20himself%20as%20a%20unique%20crusader%20against%20corruption%20claims%20made%20against%20the%20Mamata%20Banerjee%20government.%20He%20delivered%20crucial%20verdicts%20that%20have%20helped%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fbengal-ssc-recruitment-scam-how-a-focused-judge-exposed-the-racket%5C%22%3Euncover%20%3C%2Fa%3Escams%20like%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fbengal-ssc-recruitment-scam-how-a-focused-judge-exposed-the-racket%5C%22%3EBengal%20school%20recruitment%20scam.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EImtiaz%20Akhtar%2C%20an%20advocate%20in%20the%20Calcutta%20high%20court%20and%20joint%20editor%20of%20%3Cem%3ECalcutta%20Law%20Journal%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%20%3C%2Fem%3Ethat%20Gangopadhyay%E2%80%99s%20pronouncement%20that%20he%20was%20in%20touch%20with%20the%20BJP%20is%20%E2%80%9Cnothing%20but%20quid%20pro%20quo.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAs%20a%20sitting%20judge%2C%20you%20take%20an%20oath%20under%20the%20constitution%2C%20and%20by%20doing%20all%20this%20(being%20in%20touch%20with%20the%20BJP)%2C%20you%20are%20doing%20nothing%20but%20quid%20pro%20quo.%20You%20are%20saying%20that%20you%20have%20been%20in%20touch%20with%20the%20political%20masters.%20Now%20whatever%20the%20judgments%20say%2C%20regardless%20of%20merit%2C%20people%20will%20say%20this%20was%20done%20due%20to%20under-the-table%20dealing.%20This%20will%20badly%20hurt%20the%20image%20of%20the%20high%20court%20which%20is%20very%20unfortunate%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESanjoy%20Ghose%2C%20senior%20advocate%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20said%20that%20Gangopadhyay%E2%80%99s%20statement%20shows%20%E2%80%9Cabsolute%20lack%20of%20judicial%20propriety.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20shows%20an%20absolute%20lack%20of%20judicial%20propriety.%20Because%20as%20long%20as%20he%20is%20wearing%20judicial%20robes%2C%20as%20long%20as%20he%20is%20holding%20a%20constitutional%20office%20which%20requires%20absolute%20independence%2C%20justice%2C%20as%20they%20say%2C%20should%20not%20only%20be%20done%20but%20be%20seen%20to%20be%20done.%20It%20is%20actually%20a%20really%20sad%20day%20for%20the%20justice%20system%20that%20a%20sitting%20judge%20would%20say%20that%20he%20has%20contacted%20a%20political%20party%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAkhtar%20said%20that%20while%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fbengal-teacher-recruitment-scam-protesters-express-anger-at-justice-abhijit-gangulys-switch-to-bjp%5C%22%3Easpersions%20will%20be%20cast%20on%20his%20orders%3C%2Fa%3E%20now%2C%20on%20points%20of%20law%20they%20cannot%20be%20touched.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CLegally%20speaking%2C%20if%20you%20cast%20this%20politics%20aside%2C%20I%20think%20his%20orders%20are%20untouchable.%20Even%20if%20you%20go%20for%20a%20review%20or%20bring%20another%20judge%2C%20on%20points%20of%20law%20it%20is%20almost%20perfect.%20I%20think%20he%20has%20acted%20in%20great%20haste%20and%20done%20great%20harm%20to%20the%20institutional%20integrity%20and%20reputation%20of%20the%20high%20court.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENot%20new%20to%20controversies%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20not%20the%20first%20time%20that%20Gangopadhyay%20has%20been%20the%20centre%20of%20a%20political%20debate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20appointed%20as%20the%20additional%20judge%20of%20the%20Calcutta%20high%20court%20on%20May%202%2C%202018%2C%20and%20started%20functioning%20as%20a%20permanent%20judge%20of%20the%20high%20court%20on%20July%2030%2C%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20January%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-calcutta-high-court-abhijit-gangopadhyay%5C%22%3Ea%20five-judge%20bench%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20a%20special%20Saturday%20sitting%20stayed%20proceedings%20at%20the%20Calcutta%20high%20court%20in%20a%20case%20where%20a%20single-judge%20bench%20of%20Gangopadhyay%20had%20defied%20a%20stay%20order%20passed%20by%20a%20division%20bench%20of%20Justices%20Soumen%20Sen%20and%20Uday%20Kumar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGangopadhyay%E2%80%99s%20single%20judge%20bench%20had%20called%20for%20a%20CBI%20(Central%20Bureau%20of%20Investigation)%20probe%20into%20medical%20college%20admission%20irregularities%20in%20Bengal%2C%20which%20was%20stayed%20by%20the%20division%20bench%2C%20which%20was%20subsequently%20ignored%20by%20the%20now%20BJP%20leader.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20not%20the%20first%20intervention%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20matters%20related%20to%20Gangopadhyay.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20year%20in%20April%2C%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20D.Y%20Chandrachud%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsc-interview-pending-matters-calcutta-hc-abhijit-gangopadhyay%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20%E2%80%9Cjudges%20have%20no%20business%20granting%20interviews%20on%20matters%20which%20are%20pending%E2%80%9D%20in%20connection%20with%20an%20interview%20given%20by%20Gangopadhyay%20to%20a%20Bengali%20news%20channel%20in%20September%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETMC%20MP%20and%20chief%20minister%20Mamata%20Banerjee%E2%80%99s%20nephew%20Abhishek%20Banerjee%2C%20who%20is%20seen%20as%20the%20second%20in%20command%20in%20the%20party%2C%20had%20moved%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20and%20alleged%20that%20Gangopadhyay%20had%20shown%20his%20%E2%80%9Cdislike%E2%80%9D%20for%20him%20in%20the%20interview.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20matter%20came%20up%20before%20the%20apex%20court%20in%20response%20to%20Banerjee%E2%80%99s%20petition%20challenging%20the%20high%20court%20order%20against%20him%2C%20which%20had%20ordered%20an%20investigation%20by%20the%20CBI%20and%20Enforcement%20Directorate%20(ED)%20in%20connection%20with%20the%20alleged%20Bengal%20school%20jobs%20scam.%20The%20apex%20court%20had%20already%20stayed%20the%20high%20court%20against%20Banerjee%20earlier.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20apex%20court%20then%20transferred%20the%20case%20from%20Gangopadhyay.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20in%20an%20unusual%20move%2C%20Gangopadhyay%20in%20a%20%3Cem%3Esuo%20moto%3C%2Fem%3E%20order%20asked%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20Secretary%20General%20to%20provide%20him%20with%20the%20translation%20of%20his%20controversial%20media%20interview%20that%20was%20placed%20before%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20bench.%20This%20led%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20to%20hold%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fas-sc-stays-calcutta-hc-judges-direction-to-it-judicial-discipline-is-under-scrutiny%5C%22%3Especial%20sitting%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20stay%20Gangopadhyay%E2%80%99s%20direction.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFormer%20Supreme%20Court%20judge%20Madan%20B.%20Lokur%20said%20that%20while%20it%20is%20not%20possible%20to%20generalise%20on%20the%20quality%20of%20his%20orders%20given%20his%20current%20political%20turn%2C%20it%20is%20the%20apex%20court%E2%80%99s%20intervention%20in%20many%20of%20his%20cases%20%E2%80%9Cthat%20speak%20for%20itself.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20possible%20that%20some%20orders%20may%20be%20motivated.%20It%20is%20equally%20possible%20that%20they%20were%20not%20motivated.%20It%20is%20not%20possible%20to%20generalise%2C%20nor%20is%20it%20possible%20to%20come%20to%20an%20absolute%20conclusion.%20But%20let%E2%80%99s%20be%20clear%2C%20a%20trained%20legal%20mind%20can%20discern%20if%20an%20order%20is%20motivated%20or%20not.%20The%20fact%20that%20some%20cases%20were%20withdrawn%20from%20him%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20speaks%20for%20itself%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENot%20the%20first%20judge%20to%20move%20to%20politics%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGangopadhyay%20is%20not%20the%20first%20judge%20to%20move%20into%20politics%2C%20or%20even%20take%20early%20retirement%20to%20take%20the%20political%20plunge.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmong%20others%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flawmin.gov.in%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2F2015-02-02%2520-%2520JUS%2520VR%2520KRISHNA%2520IYER_0.pdf%5C%22%3EJustice%20V.R.%20Krishna%20Iyer%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20had%20been%20MLA%20in%20both%20Madras%20and%20Kerala%20(after%20the%20reorganisation%20of%20states)%2C%20was%20appointed%20to%20the%20Kerala%20high%20court%20in%201968%20and%20later%20became%20a%20Supreme%20Court%20judge%20in%201973.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Koka%20Subba%20Rao%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scobserver.in%2Fjudges%2Fjustice-koka-subba-rao%2F%5C%22%3Eresigned%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20in%201967%20after%20accepting%20the%20opposition%E2%80%99s%20invitation%20to%20contest%20the%20presidential%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFormer%20Supreme%20Court%20Justice%20Baharul%20Islam%20also%20resigned%20before%20his%20retirement%20to%20contest%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections%20from%20Barapeta%2C%20Assam%2C%20in%201983%2C%20and%20was%20subsequently%20sent%20to%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha.%20He%20had%20earlier%20also%20been%20a%20Rajya%20Sabha%20MP%20before%20being%20appointed%20as%20a%20judge%20in%20the%20Guwahati%20high%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Guman%20Mal%20Lodha%20had%20been%20the%20president%20of%20the%20Rajasthan%20unit%20of%20the%20Jana%20Sangh%20before%20being%20appointed%20as%20judge%20to%20the%20Rajasthan%20high%20court%20and%20later%20even%20contested%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20K.S.%20Hegde%2C%20who%20had%20been%20a%20Rajya%20Sabha%20MP%20on%20a%20Congress%20ticket%2C%20and%20later%20resigned%20from%20the%20post%20to%20become%20a%20judge%20in%20the%20Mysore%20high%20court%2C%20and%20subsequently%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20after%20which%20he%20again%20contested%20elections%20and%20even%20became%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20speaker%20in%201977.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMore%20recently%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fjustice-for-the-judge-injustice-for-everyone-else%5C%22%3EJustice%20Ranjan%20Gogoi%3C%2Fa%3E%20also%20became%20a%20Rajya%20Sabha%20MP%20close%20on%20the%20heels%20of%20his%20retirement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENo%20constitutional%20bar%20on%20judges%20joining%20politics%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGhose%20said%20that%20while%20history%20has%20shown%20that%20there%20have%20been%20various%20judges%20who%20have%20joined%20politics%20or%20left%20politics%20to%20become%20judges%2C%20Gangopadhyay%20has%20a%20distinction%20of%20his%20own.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20have%20been%20various%20examples%20throughout%20history%20of%20judges%20joining%20politics%20but%20a%20sitting%20judge%20has%20never%20said%20I%20am%20in%20contact%20with%20a%20political%20party%20and%20I%20am%20joining%20politics%20tomorrow%20or%20in%20two%20days%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFaizan%20Mustafa%2C%20vice%20chancellor%20of%20the%20Chanakya%20National%20Law%20University%20(CNLU)%20in%20Patna%2C%20cited%20the%20long%20list%20of%20judges%20who%20have%20taken%20the%20political%20plunge%20and%20said%20that%20while%20Gangopadhyay%E2%80%99s%20move%20has%20not%20violated%20any%20law%2C%20the%20independence%20of%20the%20judiciary%20is%20at%20stake.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20no%20cooling%20off%20period%20for%20judges%20at%20all.%20If%20people%20retire%20and%20they%20are%20nominated%20by%20the%20government%20then%20ideally%20there%20should%20be%20some%20cooling%20off%20period%20but%20as%20of%20now%20there%20is%20no%20rule.%20Anybody%20is%20free%20to%20contest%20elections%2C%20any%20citizen%20can%20do%20so.%20One%20should%20be%20more%20bothered%20about%20what%20they%20do%20as%20judges-%20were%20they%20committed%20to%20some%20ideology%20or%20some%20government%3F%20Because%20their%20performance%20as%20judges%20needs%20to%20be%20examined%20critically.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Lokur%2C%20while%20judges%20may%20have%20political%20views%2C%20they%20need%20to%20be%20kept%20aside.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20no%20constitutional%20bar%20for%20a%20judge%20to%20declare%20that%20he%20will%20resign%20and%20join%20politics%20or%20a%20political%20party.%20Judges%20are%20members%20of%20society%20and%20humans.%20They%20may%20have%20political%20views%2C%20but%20it%20is%20best%20to%20keep%20them%20aside%20while%20deciding%20a%20case%2C%20otherwise%20an%20unjust%20or%20unfair%20decision%20will%20be%20rendered.%20If%20this%20happens%2C%20it%20impacts%20the%20independence%20of%20the%20judiciary%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMustafa%20said%20that%20while%20Gangopadhyay%E2%80%99s%20judgments%20may%20not%20have%20been%20motivated%20by%20his%20future%20political%20affiliations%2C%20they%20are%20now%20open%20to%20doubts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CJudges%20live%20in%20our%20society%20and%20many%20of%20them%20talk%20to%20political%20parties%20also%20but%20ideally%2C%20when%20you%20are%20on%20the%20bench%2C%20you%20should%20be%20politically%2C%20ideologically%2C%20and%20religiously%20neutral.%20Because%20people%20ultimately%20need%20to%20have%20confidence%20in%20your%20judgment.%20Ultimately%2C%20independence%20of%20the%20judiciary%20is%20the%20right%20of%20the%20people%20rather%20than%20the%20right%20of%20judges%2C%20so%20the%20opinion%20of%20people%20matters.%20By%20making%20such%20statements%20he%20is%20creating%20doubts%20in%20the%20minds%20of%20the%20people%20about%20his%20orders%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709974321000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F09%2F20161531%2FCalcutta_High_Courtfinal.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fi-approached-bjp-why-ex-calcutta-hc-judge-abhijit-gangopadhyays-political-plunge-sparks-questions%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Once%20hailed%20as%20the%20%E2%80%98people%E2%80%99s%20judge%E2%80%99%2C%20Gangopadhyay%20is%20not%20the%20first%20judge%20to%20join%20politics%2C%20but%20his%20pronouncement%20that%20as%20a%20sitting%20judge%20he%20was%20in%20touch%20with%20the%20BJP%20has%20cast%20aspersions%20on%20his%20orders%2C%20often%20critical%20of%20the%20TMC%20government%20in%20West%20Bengal.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A24%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fi-approached-bjp-why-ex-calcutta-hc-judge-abhijit-gangopadhyays-political-plunge-sparks-questions%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Nota%20will%20have%20no%20impact%20on%20election%20results%20without%20right%20to%20reject%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709974209000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2023-11%2F20%2Ffull%2F1700502351-8725.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.busin