%20every%20square%20mile%E2%80%9D%20with%20nearly%20every%20village%20serving%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Cbase%20for%20memorable%20walks%20to%20meadows%20and%20tarns%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20242-page%20book%20has%20a%20lovely%2C%20turquoise-coloured%20Gangbal%20lake%20seen%20from%20the%20Gadsar%20pass%20on%20its%20cover%20with%20the%20mighty%20Mt%20Harmukh%20looming%20in%20the%20background.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGangbal%20is%20the%20largest%20among%20several%20dozen%20oligotrophic%20lakes%20and%20tarns%20hidden%20in%20the%20alps%20of%20Kashmir%2C%20some%20of%20which%20are%20described%20by%20the%20author%20with%20great%20love%20and%20fondness.%20British%20missionary%20and%20surgeon%20Ernest%20Neve%20remarked%20that%20these%20are%20%E2%80%9Cmost%20impressive%20pieces%20of%20mountain%20scenery%2C%20not%20only%20in%20Kashmir%2C%20but%20in%20the%20world%E2%80%9D.%20Bhattacharji%20says%20Kashmir%20is%20a%20Shangri-la%20%E2%80%9Clavishly%20gifted%20with%20glamour%20and%20beauty%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThree%20other%20chapters%20map%20some%20important%20cultural%20landmarks%2C%20Mughal%20Gardens%20and%20other%20historical%20sites%20in%20Srinagar%20and%20elsewhere%20which%20are%20poignant%20illustrations%20of%20Kashmir%E2%80%99s%20syncretic%20past%20%E2%80%93%20a%20confluence%20of%20civilisations%20which%20has%20sadly%20turned%20into%20a%20source%20of%20international%20troubles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBhattacharji%20writes%2C%20citing%20Charles%20Girdlestone%E2%80%99s%20recherch%C3%A9%20book%20%E2%80%98%3Ci%3EMemorandum%20of%20Cashmere%20and%20Adjacent%20Territories%3C%2Fi%3E%E2%80%99%3A%20%E2%80%9CTurks%20brought%20tea%2C%20silver%20and%20horses%3B%20Chinese%20brought%20earthenware%2C%20shawl%20wool%20and%20the%20%E2%80%98produce%20of%20trans-Himalayan%20looms%E2%80%99%3B%20Baltistanis%20brought%20dry%20fruits%3B%20%E2%80%98Hindustanis%E2%80%99%20brought%20chintzes%2C%20brocades%3B%20Russians%20brought%20guns%2C%20vessels%20and%20tea%20urns.%20They%20took%20away%20pashmina%2C%20iron%2C%20zafran%20and%20rice%20(from%20Kashmir).%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBurdened%20by%20a%20bureaucrat%E2%80%99s%20limitations%2C%20Bhattacharji%20believes%20that%20it%20is%20impossible%20to%20describe%20the%20beauty%20of%20Kashmir%20in%20words.%20But%20with%20his%20book%20in%20hand%2C%20one%20can%20experience%20a%20beautiful%20journey%20in%20the%20mind-boggling%20mountains%20cradling%20the%20virgin%20valleys%20of%20Kashmir%20which%20have%20been%20the%20historical%20gateways%20of%20redemption%20and%20solitude%20for%20the%20great%20Sufi%20saints%20and%20scholars%2C%20continent-cruising%20travellers%2C%20inspiration-seeking%20writers%2C%20curious%20surveyors%20and%20occasional%20alpinists.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPriced%20at%20Rs%20599%2C%20%3Cem%3EKashmir%20%E2%80%93%20Travels%20in%20Paradise%20on%20Earth%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0is%20a%20must-read%20for%20travellers%20yearning%20for%20a%20tranquil%20few%20days%20away%20from%20the%20chaos%20of%20%E2%80%98civilisation%E2%80%99.%20After%20%E2%80%98Beyond%20the%20Pir%20Panjal%E2%80%99%20by%20Neve%20and%20Garry%20Weare%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98A%20Long%20Walk%20in%20the%20Himalaya%E2%80%99%2C%20the%20book%20is%20an%20important%20addition%20to%20the%20sparse%20literature%20available%20on%20Kashmir%E2%80%99s%20rich%20natural%20landscape%20that%20can%20give%20Switzerland%20a%20run%20for%20its%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709954961000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F08175340%2FUntitled-design-35.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fa-gateway-into-scenic-and-unspoilt-landscape-of-kashmir%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Romesh%20Bhattacharji's%20latest%20book%20'Kashmir%20-%20Travels%20in%20Paradise%20on%20Earth'%20is%20a%20must-read%20for%20travellers%20yearning%20for%20a%20tranquil%20few%20days%20away%20from%20the%20chaos%20of%20%E2%80%98civilisation%E2%80%99.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A55%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fa-gateway-into-scenic-and-unspoilt-landscape-of-kashmir%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Full%20Text%20%7C%20I%20Care%20Very%20Much%20For%20India%2C%20Can't%20Control%20How%20People%20Selectively%20Quote%20Me%3A%20Nitasha%20Kaul%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F08193550%2Fkt-29-feb-b.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EWhen%20she%20arrived%20at%20Kempegowda%20airport%20in%20Bengaluru%20on%20February%2023%2C%20Nitasha%20Kaul%20was%20denied%20permission%20to%20enter%20the%20country%20even%20though%20she%20is%20an%20Overseas%20Citizen%20of%20India%20and%20has%20the%20right%20to%20come%20to%20India%20as%20often%20as%20she%20wants.%20She%20was%20given%20no%20explanation%20by%20the%20authorities%20other%20than%20that%20they%20were%20acting%20on%20the%20orders%20of%20the%20government%20in%20Delhi.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EInstead%20she%20was%20held%20in%20detention%2C%20in%20a%20small%20room%2C%20for%20almost%2024%20hours%20before%20being%20sent%20back%20to%20the%20UK.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EIn%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DJBfPhPfzkOI%5C%22%3E35-minute%20interview%20to%20Karan%20Thapar%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20%3C%2Fem%3EThe%20Wire%3Cem%3E%2C%20Kaul%2C%20who%20is%20a%20professor%20of%20politics%2C%20international%20relations%20and%20critical%20interdisciplinary%20studies%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Westminster%20in%20the%20UK%2C%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20was%20treated%20like%20a%20criminal%2C%E2%80%9D%20adding%20her%20detention%20and%20deportation%20was%20%E2%80%9Cunjust%20and%20unfair%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Ca%20harrowing%20experience%E2%80%9D%20for%20her.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EKaul%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3Esaid%3A%20%E2%80%9CI%20consider%20myself%20Indian%2C%20I%20care%20very%20much%20for%20India%E2%80%9D.%20She%20comprehensively%20responded%20t