n%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjamanetwork.com%2Fjournals%2Fjamaneurology%2Ffullarticle%2F2810957%5C%22%3EFramingham%20Heart%20Study%3C%2Fa%3E%20were%20assessed%20using%20a%20sleep%20recording%20%E2%80%94%20known%20as%20polysomnography%20%E2%80%94%20on%20two%20occasions%2C%20approximately%20five%20years%20apart%2C%20in%201995-1998%20and%20again%20in%202001-2003.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20people%20showed%20a%20reduction%20in%20their%20deep%20slow-wave%20sleep%20over%20the%20years%2C%20as%20is%20to%20be%20expected%20with%20ageing.%20Conversely%2C%20the%20amount%20of%20deep%20sleep%20in%20some%20people%20remained%20stable%20or%20even%20increased.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOur%20team%20of%20researchers%20from%20the%20Framingham%20Heart%20Study%20followed%20346%20participants%20aged%2060%20and%20over%20for%20a%20further%2017%20years%20to%20observe%20who%20developed%20dementia%20and%20who%20did%20not.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EProgressive%20loss%20of%20deep%20sleep%20over%20time%20was%20associated%20with%20an%20increased%20risk%20of%20dementia%2C%20whatever%20the%20cause%2C%20and%20particularly%20Alzheimer%E2%80%99s%20type%20dementia.%20These%20results%20were%20independent%20of%20many%20other%20risk%20factors%20for%20dementia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlthough%20our%20results%20do%20not%20prove%20that%20loss%20of%20deep%20sleep%20causes%20dementia%2C%20they%20do%20suggest%20that%20it%20could%20be%20a%20risk%20factor%20in%20the%20elderly.%20Other%20aspects%20of%20sleep%20may%20also%20be%20important%2C%20such%20as%20its%20duration%20and%20quality.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EStrategies%20to%20improve%20deep%20sleep%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKnowing%20the%20impact%20of%20a%20lack%20of%20deep%20sleep%20on%20cognitive%20health%2C%20what%20strategies%20can%20be%20used%20to%20improve%20it%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFirst%20and%20foremost%2C%20if%20you%E2%80%99re%20experiencing%20sleep%20problems%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20worth%20talking%20to%20your%20doctor.%20Many%20sleep%20disorders%20are%20underdiagnosed%20and%20treatable%2C%20particularly%20through%20behavioural%20(i.e.%20non-medicinal)%20approaches.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdopting%20good%20sleep%20habits%20can%20help%2C%20such%20as%20going%20to%20bed%20and%20getting%20up%20at%20consistent%20times%20or%20avoiding%20bright%20or%20blue%20light%20in%20bed%2C%20like%20that%20of%20screens.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYou%20can%20also%20avoid%20caffeine%2C%20limit%20your%20alcohol%20intake%2C%20maintain%20a%20healthy%20weight%2C%20be%20physically%20active%20during%20the%20day%2C%20and%20sleep%20in%20a%20comfortable%2C%20dark%20and%20quiet%20environment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20role%20of%20deep%20sleep%20in%20preventing%20dementia%20remains%20to%20be%20explored%20and%20studied.%20Encouraging%20sleep%20with%20good%20lifestyle%20habits%20could%20have%20the%20potential%20to%20help%20us%20age%20in%20a%20healthier%20way.%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Conversation%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcounter.theconversation.com%2Fcontent%2F222854%2Fcount.gif%3Fdistributor%3Drepublish-lightbox-basic%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAndr%C3%A9e-Ann%20Baril%20is%C2%A0Professeure-chercheure%20adjointe%20au%20D%C3%A9partement%20de%20m%C3%A9decine%2C%20Universit%C3%A9%20de%20Montr%C3%A9al%20and%20Matthew%20Pase%20is%C2%A0Associate%20Professor%20of%20Neurology%20and%20Epidemiology%2C%20Monash%20University.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20is%20republished%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%5C%22%3EThe%20Conversation%3C%2Fa%3E%20under%20a%20Creative%20Commons%20license.%20Read%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fbetter-sleep-is-a-protective-factor-against-dementia-222854%5C%22%3Eoriginal%20article%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709947841000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F08154912%2Fmatheus-vinicius-kHHwYNA1lnM-uns